  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "He built Elath,.... A port which belonged to Edom, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 2:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " which very probably David took from them when he made them tributary, and which they retook when they revolted, and Amaziah got again when he defeated them; and this his son rebuilt and fortified: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and restored it to Judah; annexed it to the kingdom of Judah, as in the days of David and Solomon: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "after that the king slept with his fathers; after the death of his father Amaziah. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "after that the king slept with his fathers; after the death of his father Amaziah. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
